On Fri, 1 Aug 2003, gil hayes wrote:

> With all this paint discussion, I picked up on a string where someone said
> "(paraphrased) you can go to an auto/paint supply store and get them to mix
> your color and put it in shaker cans."
> 
> Is that just for the camper top, or are you saying that one of those places
> will put them in handheld spray cans and you can then paint an entire bus
> and make it look really good?

I have used the "PreVal" bottles and they are ok for touch up but the cost
of painting a bus with them would be astronomical they weren't cheap.  and
while the "jars" are reusable they require a can of propelant that is
rather pricy...figure about $10 a load.    

